{
  "texts": [
    "The fibre M b is a flat Gaussian soliton, and its vector field is the Euler vector field (the one whose flow is given by scalar multiplication).",
    "In terms of the potential, we havef (b, v) = 1 2 |v| 2 h(b), b ∈ U ⊂ B, v ∈ R n,in a local trivialisation U × R n adapted to the flat connection.",
    "Extending v to be covariantly parallel in horizontal directions, and using that f is horizontally constant, we deduce that h is preserved by the flat connection.",
    "This in particular implies that the monodromy ρ takes values in O(n).",
    "The converse is clear.If N is nilpotent and non-abelian, it suffices to show that the fibres are non-gradient solitons."
  ]
}